(firstQuint)Combination of Cryosurgery and NK Immunotherapy for Advanced Non-Small Cell Lung Cancer.

 By enrolling patients with NSCLC adapted to enrolled criteria, this study will document for the first time the safety and the short and long term efficacy of the combined therapy using cryosurgery and nature killer (NK) cells for NSCLC.

 The safety will be evaluated by statistics of adverse reactions.

 The efficacy will be evaluated according to local relief degree, progress free survival (PFS) and overall survival (OS).

